Uncanny X-Men (1963) #1
results.description: The master of magnetism has taken over a missile base, and only the strangest teens of all time stand between him and victory! It's the X-Men's first day of class, and Magneto wants to make it a memorable one - and their last!

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #10
results.description: When a trip to the South Pole yields a jungle adventure, the X-Men meet Ka-Zar, lord of the Savage Land!

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #100
results.description: The X-Men are aboard a space station with Stephen Lang, the director of an anti-mutant project known simply as Armageddon. Armageddon’s goal? To wipe out all earth’s mutants from the far-reaches of space! In such close quarters, tempers will surely flare.

results.title: Greater Love Hath No X-Man...
results.description: The X-Men have to battle the X-Sentinels to free their captured comrades; The space station is damaged in the fight, and Jean has to guide the Shuttle back to earth herself knowing the strain will kill her.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #101
results.description: The X-Men are re-entering Earth's atmosphere aboard a crippled Starcore space shuttle with Jean Grey piloting the ship.

results.title: Like a Phoenix, From the Ashes!
results.description: The X-Men's shuttle crash lands in Jamaica Bay and Jean rises from the wreckage as the Phoenix; To facilitate Jean's recovery, Prof X sends all of the X-Men but Cyclops to Scotland on vacation where Banshee has just inherited his ancestral castle; The X-Men show up at the castle and find it already inhabited by Sean's cousin Tom and his pal Juggy.  Of course, as all now know, Jean and Phoenix are two separate entities (the latter taking the former for a template), and not the same being as the story insinuates.

results.description: The X-Men's trip to Cassidy Keep has been interrupted by an attack from Black Tom and the Juggernaut, who seek to kill the group of mutants.

results.title: Who Will Stop the Juggernaut?
results.description: Under the influence of claustrophobia, Storm re-lives her origin; The rest of the X-Men come up short in knocking out Black Tom and Juggernaut.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #103
results.description: Following his defeat at the hands of Black Tom and the Juggernaut, Nightcrawler's unconscious body is pulled through the secret passageways of Cassidy Keep by a group of Leprechauns. When Nightcrawler awakens, he is finds himself surrounded by creatures that he thought were creatures of myth…

results.title: The Fall of the Tower
results.description: The X-Men are assisted in their fight against Black Tom and Juggernaut by Leprechauns ?!?

results.title: The Gentleman's Name is Magneto
results.description: The X-Men head to Muir Island to make sure everything is fine there and discover that Eric the Red has grown Magneto back to adulthood (and Maggie isn't a very happy camper).

results.title: Phoenix Unleashed!
results.description: Eric dupes Firelord into helping him fight the X-Men, but Jean manifests her Phoenix powers once again to counter the threat; Lilandra arrives on Earth but is captured by Eric; Xavier sends the X-Men through a space portal to rescue Lilandra.

results.title: Dark Shroud of the Past !
results.description: The X-Men are working out in the Danger Room when the evil aspect of Xavier's mind attacks them with versions of the old X-Men.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #107
results.description: After being transported through a star-gate by Phoenix, the X-Men find themselves on an ancient planet that is home to the M'Kraan Crystal, surrounded by several members of the Shi’ar Imperial Guard serving the evil Emperor D’Ken.

results.title: Where No X-Man Has Gone Before!
results.description: The X-Men try to save Lilandra from her evil cousin who is trying to use the M'Kraan Crystal to achieve ultimate power, but the Imperial Guard get in the way; The Starjammers show up to the rescue.

results.title: Uncanny X-Men (1963) #108
results.description: With Emperor D'Ken threatening to destroy the universe while trying to utilize the power of the M'Kraan Crystal, the X-Men and the Starjammers discover that when the specific stars come into alignment, the crystal will become available to D'Ken.

results.title: Armageddon Now !
results.description: The X-Men and Starjammers are forced to battle the Crystal Guardians to try and gain access to the M'Kraan Crystal; Jean manifests awesome power as the Phoenix and saves the universe from destruction; Corsair is Cyclops' father.
